Q. Float vs Double — what did you use and why?
A =>  For storing co-ordinates I used float to save memory
      But for area and volume used double because if we are accumulating numbers and precision is not there solutions will change drastically over long terms

Q. Time complexity of your area and volume computation?
A =>  For area linear => no of triangle
      For volume => no of points x log N
  
Q.  What is the memory footprint of 1M triangles?
A =>  Example thinking:
      Each triangle:
        3 vertices. Each vertex = 3 doubles (8 bytes each) = 3 × 3 × 8 = 72 bytes
        normal (3 doubles = 24 bytes)
        Total: ~96 bytes per triangle
      1M triangles ≈ 96 MB
      So if you store all the in vector and vector gets full. How that works? (how vector grows internally?)
      Where this memory is stored. In RAM? how much RAM would it takes at 10M then?

Q. How would you scale this to 100M triangles?
A =>  Streaming, Memory mapping, Parallelization

Q. What is the difference between triangle mesh (STL) and B-Rep modeling?
A =>  A collection of flat triangles
      Faces (surfaces), Edges (curves), Vertices (points). Easy to edit parametrically. It's needed for boolean operation.

A => Again it's not most efficient solution my goal is to keep pushing just to see how much can I optimize it in single thread. 

*******  MOST IMPORTANT QUESTION    ******
What did you learn from profiler and how you improved your solution?
A => So even today for 1M triangle it takes around 10 -15 sec for volume computation
Reason is the current code is calling basic vector function too many times actually it's making 1 Billion calls (LOL!!!)
We need to make this most frequent methods
    => make small methods inline
    => put them in header only file so cpp never gets involved
    => Use operator overload if possible
    => Avoid any temporary objection creation in methods everything should be via reference

This seems very basic but once you hit bottle necks in production then you realize how to use them and then you will mostly never forget them in life !!!

